title: 4 Shot, 2 Killed In South Memphis Apartment Complex
content:
(Memphis) Memphis police are on the scene of a deadly shooting in the Woodbridge Crossing Apartments.
MPD Spokesperson Sgt. Alyssa Macon-Moore tells WREG officers were called to the scene in 2300 block of Ketchum just before 7:00 p.m. Sunday night.
They found three people suffering from gunshot wounds. They were taken to The Med by ambulance. Another victim had been taken to the Med by private vehicle.
Two of those victims have since been pronounced dead.
No arrests have been made.
We have a crew on this scene gathering information and will bring you the latest information on WREG News Channel 3 at 10:00 p.m.
